 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21296","referenceCode":"21M.3.AHL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that P0P1×P0P2=3.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}